Create a module that:
1. Identifies and selects the DOM elements containing the Tomatometer and Popcorn Meter scores
2. Extracts the percentage values from these elements
3. Handles cases where one or both scores might not be available
4. Returns the extracted scores as numbers

```javascript
// scoreExtractor.js
export function extractScores() {
  // Robust selectors for Tomatometer and Popcorn Meter
  // These selectors may need adjustment based on actual RT DOM structure
  const tomatoMeterEl = document.querySelector('.tomatometer .percentage');
  const popcornMeterEl = document.querySelector('.audience-score .percentage');

  // Extract and parse scores
  const tomatoMeter = tomatoMeterEl ? parseInt(tomatoMeterEl.textContent, 10) : null;
  const popcornMeter = popcornMeterEl ? parseInt(popcornMeterEl.textContent, 10) : null;

  return { tomatoMeter, popcornMeter };
}
```

Implement a MutationObserver to detect when scores become available on the page, as RT is an SPA:

```javascript
export function observeScoreElements(callback) {
  const observer = new MutationObserver((mutations) => {
    // Check if score elements are now in the DOM
    const { tomatoMeter, popcornMeter } = extractScores();
    if (tomatoMeter !== null && popcornMeter !== null) {
      callback({ tomatoMeter, popcornMeter });
    }
  });

  // Observe the entire document for changes
  observer.observe(document.body, { childList: true, subtree: true });
  return observer;
}
```

Create a module that:
1. Takes the extracted Tomatometer and Popcorn Meter scores as input
2. Calculates the difference (Popcorn Meter - Tomatometer)
3. Returns the calculated Reel Score

```javascript
// reelScoreCalculator.js
export function calculateReelScore(popcornMeter, tomatoMeter) {
  // Handle cases where one or both scores might be missing
  if (popcornMeter === null || tomatoMeter === null) {
    return null;
  }

  // Calculate the difference
  return popcornMeter - tomatoMeter;
}

// Determine the visual representation based on the score
export function getReelScoreVisuals(reelScore) {
  if (reelScore === null) {
    return { color: '#95a5a6', icon: 'neutral', description: 'Score unavailable' };
  }

  if (reelScore > 0) {
    return {
      color: '#2ecc71', // Green
      icon: 'thumbs-up',
      description: `Audience score is ${Math.abs(reelScore)}% higher than critics.`
    };
  } else if (reelScore < 0) {
    return {
      color: '#e74c3c', // Red
      icon: 'thumbs-down',
      description: `Audience score is ${Math.abs(reelScore)}% lower than critics.`
    };
  } else {
    return {
      color: '#95a5a6', // Gray
      icon: 'neutral',
      description: 'Critics and audiences agree exactly.'
    };
  }
}
```

